The paper deals with the problem of estimating Gaussian sources over Gaussian multiple access channels (MAC) using joint source and channel coding. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses power minimization problems and optimization techniques, which are relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.NI). The topic of energy efficiency is also addressed, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper deals with the asymptotic behavior of the proposed approach, which is relevant to statistical theory (cs.ST).
